data.text:
Susannah Harker (born 26 April 1965[1]) voiced Clare Keightley in the webcast production of Shada and the audio version of the story and Anya in the Big Finish audio story Eye of Darkness.

Career[]

Harker was also featured in the Big Finish Productions revival of Sapphire & Steel, in which she played Sapphire opposite David Warner as Steel.

Personal life[]

She is the daughter of Polly Adams, sister of Caroline Harker and sister-in-law of Anthony Calf. She was married to Iain Glen for nine years and was also in a relationship with Paul McGann for two years.
